section.section:
Assistance shall be provided to an applicant or recipient under this subtitle only if the applicant or recipient:
resides in the State at the time of application for assistance;
if applicable:
has applied for child support services with the appropriate local child support enforcement office at the time of application for assistance; and
complies with the requirements of the local child support enforcement office;
has engaged in job search activities as requested by the Department;
participates in work activity under this subtitle; and
meets all other FIP requirements that the Secretary establishes by regulation.
